{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 00:14:48.828302", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nScope and goal\n- Topology: EBGP Clos (super-spine AS 65000, spines, leaves). Each leaf connects a /24 host subnet 10.<pod>.<leaf>.0/24 and advertises it via BGP. Inter-router links are /31 in 172.16.0.0/16.\n- Focus: Validate overall fabric health, detect anomalies, localize faulty devices, and identify the root cause (no remediation steps).\n\nSummary of health\n- Fabric control plane: Healthy. All examined BGP sessions between leaves, spines, and the super-spine are Established with prefixes exchanged.\n- End-host segment 10.0.0.0/24 (pc_0_0): Healthy. Correct IP, default route present; fabric reachability tests from many hosts succeed.\n- End-host segment 10.0.1.0/24 (pc_0_1): Broken. The host is not provisioned with a NIC/IP; it is effectively disconnected from the fabric.\n\nKey observations and evidence\n\n1) Reachability tests\n- Global reachability snapshot shows pc_0_1 has no IP and no tests executed from it:\n  - hosts: pc_0_1 has null IP; status “unknown” in test matrix entries involving pc_0_1.\n- Numerous other hosts in the wider lab can reach each other and 10.0.4.2 / 10.1.7.2 with 0% loss, indicating the spine/super-spine/leaf fabric is operating normally.\n\n2) pc_0_1 host state (fault localized at host)\n- Network config on pc_0_1:\n  - Only loopback exists. ip link/ip addr show and /sys/class/net list only “lo”; no eth0 or any NIC present.\n  - No IP address or default route.\n  - Conclusion: pc_0_1 is not connected to the leaf; it has no host-facing interface at all.\n\n3) Leaf router facing pc_0_1 (leaf_router_0_1)\n- Host-facing interface: eth8 has 10.0.1.1/24 configured and is UP/LOWER_UP.\n- BGP state: Established to all upstream neighbors (8 peers), receiving/sending full set of prefixes.\n- Routing table contains BGP routes to all other pod/leaf /24s; 10.0.1.0/24 present locally as connected on eth8.\n- Data-plane probe to host:\n  - leaf_router_0_1 -> 10.0.1.2 (pc_0_1 expected IP): 100% packet loss, “Destination Host Unreachable” from 10.0.1.1.\n  - ARP/ND on eth8 shows no neighbor entries for the host.\n- Etthtool indicates link “detected: yes” on eth8, but absence of a peer (and the host having no NIC) shows the host side is not present; the leaf’s interface is configured but effectively has no attached end host.\n\n4) pc_0_0 and its leaf (leaf_router_0_0)\n- pc_0_0 has eth0 10.0.0.2/24 with default via 10.0.0.1; traffic in the fabric works normally per reachability tests.\n- leaf_router_0_0 BGP summary: all neighbors Established; prefixes received and sent as expected.\n\n5) Spine and super-spine control plane\n- spine_router_0_0 and spine_router_0_1: BGP Established to super-spine and leaves; prefixes received; stable Up/Down timers.\n- super_spine_router_0: BGP Established to multiple spines with prefixes received; no signs of systemic control plane issues.\n\nAnomalies detected\n- pc_0_1 is missing its host-facing NIC and IP configuration entirely (only loopback present). This is inconsistent with the topology that expects leaf_router_0_1:eth2 (host-facing) connected to pc_0_1:eth0.\n- As a result, leaf_router_0_1 cannot reach 10.0.1.2; the 10.0.1.0/24 segment is effectively unpopulated.\n\nFault localization\n- Faulty device: pc_0_1 (end host).\n- Fabric elements (leaf_router_0_1, spines, super-spine) show normal BGP operation and routing; no evidence of faults in the underlay.\n\nRoot cause\n- Provisioning/cabling error on the host segment for 10.0.1.0/24:\n  - pc_0_1 is not provisioned with a network interface (eth0) and thus has no IP (expected 10.0.1.2/24).\n  - The leaf’s host-facing interface exists and is configured (10.0.1.1/24) but has no connected peer, causing ARP resolution to fail and leading to “Destination Host Unreachable” when probing 10.0.1.2.\n\nImpact assessment\n- All traffic to/from the 10.0.1.0/24 network (pc_0_1) is unreachable.\n- The rest of the Clos fabric and other subnets are unaffected and operating normally.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 18808, "output_tokens": 4253, "total_tokens": 23061, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 18048}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 3136}}}
